column1: ORIGID: Original Identifier - a unique code or number assigned to each data entry.
CountyName: The name of the county.
PopulationCensus16: The population of the county as recorded in the 2016 census.人口数量
IGEasting and IGNorthing: Coordinates in the Irish Grid Reference System (IGRS), used for mapping in Ireland.网格参考系统
Lat and Long: Latitude and Longitude - geographic coordinates indicating the location.纬度和经度
UniqueGeographicIdentifier: A unique identifier for geographic locations.地理位置的唯一标识符
ConfirmedCovidCases: The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in the area. 该地区确认的COVID-19病例数
PopulationProportionCovidCases: The proportion of the population that has been confirmed with COVID-19.已确认感染COVID-19的人口比例
ConfirmedCovidDeaths: The number of confirmed deaths due to COVID-19 in the area.确认的COVID-19死亡病例数
ConfirmedCovidRecovered: The number of people who have recovered from COVID-19.已从COVID-19中恢复的人数
x and y: Typically, these represent coordinate points in a spatial dataset, though their specific meaning would depend on the context of this table.
FID: Feature Identifier - often used in geographic information systems (GIS) to uniquely identify features.
TimeStampDate: The date and time when the data was recorded or last updated.数据记录或最后更新的日期和时间
